<doc id="991605" wikidata="Q953130" url="?curid=991605" title="Marcus Tullius Decula">
<text>Marcus Tullius Decula was a consul of the Roman Republic in 81 BC alongside Gnaeus Cornelius Dolabella, during the dictatorship of Sulla; but the consuls of that year were only nominal, as Sulla had all the power in his hands. (Cic. &quot;de Leg. Ayr.&quot; ii. 14 ; Gellius, xv. 28 ; Appian, &quot;B. C.&quot; i. 100.)

His father was perhaps Marcus Tullius, &quot;triumvir monetalis&quot; in 120 BC.

